# Human-readable reference only — not read by Alchemy CLI for all keys; use real `.env.local` / `.env.production` (gitignored).
# Local dev: `bun run dev` (Turbo runs `alchemy dev --app <id>` for the web + each deployable worker package; see root README).
# Deploy: `bun run deploy`. See https://alchemy.run/getting-started/ and https://alchemy.run/concepts/state/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Local — repo-root `.env.local`
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Cloudflare — optional locally if you use `bunx wrangler login` / `bun alchemy login`. Required for many CI flows.
# CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=
# CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID=

# Alchemy — required. Encrypts `alchemy.secret()` in state (see https://alchemy.run/concepts/secret/#encryption-password)
# Set in `.env.local` (run `bun run setup`) or `.env.production` / CI (`bun run setup:prod` seeds the file with random values).
# Use a strong, stable value in production, CI, and any shared or long-lived state.
# ALCHEMY_PASSWORD=

# Secret binding example — required. Shared by the web worker and chatroom worker.
# The browser never receives this value; the web worker uses it when forwarding `/api/ws/*` to the chatroom DO.
# CHATROOM_INTERNAL_SECRET=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Production / CI — repo-root `.env.production` (optional if you only pass env in CI)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Same Cloudflare vars as needed for `bun alchemy deploy`.
# For CI with the default filesystem state store, you may need:
# ALCHEMY_CI_STATE_STORE_CHECK=false
# (Prefer a remote state store for real pipelines — https://alchemy.run/concepts/state/)
